<!-- Problem Statement -->

<section>
<h2>Project Problem Statement</h2>

<p>
Employee attrition is one of the most critical workforce challenges in
high-skill cybersecurity organizations such as Palo Alto Networks.
Excessive employee turnover results in loss of expertise, increased hiring
costs, project disruptions, and reduced organizational productivity.
This project identifies workforce attrition patterns and risk hotspots
across departments, job roles, demographics, tenure groups, and workload
factors.
</p>

</section>

<!-- Project Objectives -->

<section>
<h2>Project Objectives</h2>

<ul>
<li>Calculate overall organizational attrition rate.</li>
<li>Identify departments with high employee turnover.</li>
<li>Analyze attrition by job role.</li>
<li>Study demographic attrition patterns.</li>
<li>Analyze tenure-based employee exits.</li>
<li>Measure impact of overtime and business travel.</li>
<li>Provide recommendations for retention strategies.</li>
</ul>

