<!-- Recommendations -->

<section>
<h2>Recommendations</h2>

<ul>
<li>Reduce excessive overtime workload.</li>
<li>Strengthen onboarding programs for new employees.</li>
<li>Provide clear career growth opportunities.</li>
<li>Improve employee engagement initiatives.</li>
<li>Increase promotion transparency.</li>
<li>Monitor high-risk departments monthly.</li>
<li>Conduct employee satisfaction surveys regularly.</li>
<li>Introduce retention incentives for critical talent.</li>
</ul>

</section>

<!-- Conclusion -->

<section>
<h2>Conclusion</h2>

<p>
The analysis highlights that employee attrition is concentrated among
early-career employees, sales-focused roles, employees working overtime,
and those with frequent travel responsibilities. By implementing targeted
retention strategies and continuously monitoring workforce analytics,
Palo Alto Networks can significantly reduce employee turnover and improve
organizational performance.
</p>

